          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EXTB"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "Three physical processes were identified that could",
                "lead to systematic errors. These  are  spontaneous",
                "fission, thermal neutron fission in 235U and",
                "attenuation of fragments in the oxide layer of the 238U",
                "foil. A calculation for both 238U and 232Th with",
                "spontaneous fission half-lives of 1.02e16 y and",
                "1.39e18 y would account for only 0.072% and 0.00053% of",
                "the expected number of fission events. To estimate",
                "thermal neutron fission in 235U, 93% enriched 235U foil",
                "was placed in the beam produced by a Cr target in a",
                "manner identical to that of the depleted 238U foil. The",
                "resulting track density did not vary by more than one",
                "standard deviation from the results obtained with the",
                "depleted 238U foil. To estimate attenuation of fission",
                "fragments in the black oxide layer, two separate runs",
                "were made in gamma ray beams produced by the Cr and Ti",
                "targets with a uranium foil that had its oxide layer",
                "removed. The results from these two runs did not",
                "deviate from the other results by more than one",
                "standard deviation.",
                "state nuclear track detectors, the photoneutrons",
                "from (gamma,n) and (gamma,f) reactions were detected",
                "by 4pi long counter of  a Halpern type with  4 BF3",
                "detectors immersed  in paraffin. The efficiency of the",
                "detector was determined by placing a 1.0Ci PuBe source",
                "and was calculated to be 2.15%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TRD",
                "BF3"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The fission events are recorded with solid",
                "state nuclear track detectors, the photoneutrons",
                "from (gamma,n) and (gamma,f) reactions were detected",
                "by 4pi long counter of  a Halpern type with  4 BF3",
                "detectors immersed  in paraffin. The efficiency of the",
                "detector was determined by placing a 1.0Ci PuBe source",
                "and was calculated to be 2.15%."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " For determination of contributions of water",
                "and Al to the capture gamma ray spectra.",
                "The  intensity of the beam was monitored with LiF",
                "thermoluminescent dosimeters."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
